cussion; 2-10s apply cost has 5x spread without UX-acceptability discussion."], "dispositions": {"apply": 3, "dismiss": 4, "ask": 1}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised intent statement to use source language: 'close the post-epic-113 regression where users drift behind on cortex CLI fixes because the upgrade verb is manual' (replacing the 'zero-friction CLI updates' paraphrase).", "Revised requirements alignment from 'Aligned' to 'Partial alignment: project.md documents per-repo settings.local.json sandbox registration; ticket extends settings_merge.py flow to additionally register a user-global ${XDG_STATE_HOME}/cortex-command/ path — semantic deviation worth flagging for research.'", "Strengthened complexity reasoning to cite multiple complex-tier signals: cross-cutting behavioral effects on every SessionStart and every cortex CLI invocation, introduces new state-dir convention and env-var contract, requires design trade-offs around dev-mode predicates and apply gating, modifies shared infrastructure (the SessionStart chain). File count alone is the weakest of these signals."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "Ticket's Out-of-Scope section defines Shape 1 ('Background fire-and-forget apply ... rejected per design review — introduces mid-session breakage, requires active-session detection that doesn't map cleanly, separate failure-visibility surface') and Shape 2 ('LaunchAgent daemon ... ticket 112 currently parked pending CLI shape; Shape 3 delivers the same UX without the daemon') inline. A reader of the ticket alone can identify both alternatives and their rejection rationales."}, {"finding_index": 4, "rationale": "Source provides per-component rationale for each Shape 3 mechanism: daily throttle (avoid 200ms hot path on every SessionStart), flock -n (parallel-session safety, matches existing cortex pattern in settings_merge.py), BSD vs GNU stat branching (Mac dev + Linux deployment portability), three dev-mode predicates (each catches a distinct dev scenario), sticky flag (retry semantics without user re-trigger). Each component is well-motivated; complexity is contextual, not gratuitous."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "Mitigations are present in source: timeout 5 prevents hang, flock -n prevents deadlock, daily throttle limits frequency, three dev-mode predicates skip in active development, sticky flag makes failure visible, documented disable mechanism (CORTEX_DEV_MODE=1 or hook deletion). Staged rollout doesn't apply per project.md ('Primarily personal tooling, shared publicly for others to clone or fork')."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Baselines support the feasibility claim at intent-clarity level (200ms daily check is acceptable for SessionStart; 2-10s apply gated on user-initiated cortex invocation is acceptable per source's rationale 'the user is already synchronously waiting for that command'). Comprehensive edge-case modeling (flaky networks, slow apply UX) is research/spec phase territory, not clarify."}], "status": "ok"}
